questions.question:
A company is using IAM policy to manage access to AWS services and resources. Your teammate has recently resigned and handed over a set of CloudFormation templates that she is maintaining to you. You checked the templates and looked at the configured IAM policy for an S3 bucket.

What does the following IAM policy allow? (Select TWO.)

{
   "Version": "2012-10-17",
   "Statement": [
     {
       "Effect": "Allow",
       "Action": [
         "s3:Get*",
         "s3:List*"
       ],
      "Resource": "*"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "s3:PutObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::tutorialsdojo/*"
    }
  ]
}
